This Presidential Memorandum, issued on August 3, 2020, extends the use of the National Guard in responding to COVID-19 and facilitating economic recovery. It emphasizes the importance of cooperation between the federal government and states in addressing the threat of COVID-19 and supporting vulnerable populations. The memorandum extends the 100 percent federal cost share for the State of Texas' use of National Guard forces until December 31, 2020. This includes duty necessary to comply with health protection protocols recommended by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and other agreed-upon measures. The memorandum also includes general provisions that clarify its implementation and do not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States. The Secretary of Defense is directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.